<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-744-668  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 744 668.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 6 1990 n380 pS45(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Making history with color: a new breed of color peripheralsinspires a generation of innovative users.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Peterson, Tami.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Thanks to new high-resolution color monitors and color calibrationsoftware, many newspapers are now able to include color images asquickly and easily as traditional monochrome pictures.andP;  Colorimages are often captured off of video tape, which saves the timeinvolved in developing traditional color film.andP;  The digitizedimage is color-corrected on a dual-page monitor using a colorimage editor, which also performs the four-color separationrequired for printing.andP;  By using color calibration software,publishers can eliminate the need to create a color key becausethey can be confident that their monitors reflect actual printedcolors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ColorMonitorsNewspapersPublishing IndustryHardware SelectionColor Separation.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>